Other objects, advantages and novel features of the present invention will become apparent from the following detailed description of the invention when considered in conjunction with the accompanying drawings.


BRIEF DESCRIPTION OF THE DRAWINGS


FIG. 1 is a view of a system for measuring and displaying the operation of a synchronization in the case of a shift-operated vehicle;


FIG. 2 is a flow chart of the process for determining the relative movement of the participating components;


FIG. 3 is a diagram of the measuring precision and the tolerance of measuring chains;


FIG. 4 is a view of the angle of rotation range of the synchronizing ring relative to the movement of the sliding sleeve;


FIG. 5 is a photo-realistic display of the observed components of a synchronizing device as used in the illustrated measuring process.
